### Describe the bug

This issue does seem to have a workaround -- using the `DefaultJavaPrettyPrinter` with optimized parenthesis turned on. However, when used with the default settings, we get extra (and incorrect) parenthesis when the source code below is pretty-printed. 

The inspiration of the source code is from https://github.com/INRIA/spoon/issues/5001, where we have the complex SQL Query String. I believe for the actual output, we should get the same string below, maybe without the neat demarcation into new lines for the long string? 

